# Coding Standards

## Architecture ‚Äî MVVM + Clean Layers

Strictly enforce three layers. **Never** let a layer reach across its boundary.

| Layer | Allowed to know about |
|---|---|
| **View** (`ui/‚Ä¶Fragment`, `ui/‚Ä¶Activity`, `adapters/`) | ViewModel only ‚Äî observe `LiveData`, call ViewModel methods |
| **ViewModel** (`ui/‚Ä¶ViewModel`) | Repository only ‚Äî no `Context` unless unavoidable (`AndroidViewModel`) |
| **Data** (`data/repository/`, `data/remote/`, `data/local/`) | Data sources only ‚Äî no Android UI imports |

```kotlin
// ‚ùå BAD ‚Äî Fragment directly touches a repository
class HomeFragment : Fragment() {
    private val repo = PostRepository()
    fun load() { repo.getPosts() }
}

// ‚úÖ GOOD ‚Äî Fragment observes ViewModel
class HomeFragment : Fragment() {
    private val vm: HomeViewModel by activityViewModels { HomeViewModelFactory(...) }
    override fun onViewCreated(...) {
        vm.posts.observe(viewLifecycleOwner) { render(it) }
    }
}
```

## Separation of Concerns

- **Fragments / Activities** ‚Äî only UI logic: binding, navigation, observing LiveData, showing dialogs/toasts.
- **ViewModels** ‚Äî only business / presentation logic: state management, coroutine launching, calling repositories.
- **Repositories** ‚Äî only data coordination: deciding between remote and local cache, mapping entities ‚Üí domain models.
- **Data sources** (`FirestoreDataSource`, `*Dao`) ‚Äî raw data access only; no business logic.
- **Utils** ‚Äî pure helpers with no side effects; avoid placing logic here that belongs in a ViewModel or Repository.

## Resource Wrapper ‚Äî Use for All Async Results

Always return `Resource<T>` from repositories and expose it via `LiveData` in ViewModels.

```kotlin
// ‚úÖ Repository
suspend fun getPost(id: String): Resource<Post> = try {
    Resource.Success(remote.fetchPost(id))
} catch (e: Exception) {
    Resource.Error(e.localizedMessage ?: "Unknown error")
}

// ‚úÖ ViewModel
fun loadPost(id: String) {
    viewModelScope.launch {
        _post.value = Resource.Loading()
        _post.value = repository.getPost(id)
    }
}
```

## View Binding

Always use the nullable backing field pattern. Never hold a binding reference beyond `onDestroyView`.

```kotlin
// ‚úÖ GOOD
private var _binding: FragmentHomeBinding? = null
private val binding get() = _binding!!

override fun onCreateView(...): View {
    _binding = FragmentHomeBinding.inflate(inflater, container, false)
    return binding.root
}

override fun onDestroyView() {
    super.onDestroyView()
    _binding = null
}
```

## Coroutines

- Launch coroutines from `viewModelScope` in ViewModels only.
- Use `Dispatchers.IO` for database/network, `Dispatchers.Main` for UI updates.
- Prefer `Flow` in repositories; collect in ViewModels using `asLiveData()` or explicit `launch`.
- Cancel jobs explicitly when replacing them (pagination, search).

```kotlin
// ‚úÖ Cancel previous job before launching a new one
private var fetchJob: Job? = null
fun refresh() {
    fetchJob?.cancel()
    fetchJob = viewModelScope.launch { ... }
}
```

## Kotlin Style

- Follow `kotlin.code.style=official` (already set in `gradle.properties`).
- Prefer `val` over `var`; use `var` only when mutation is required.
- Use named arguments for calls with 3+ parameters.
- No magic numbers ‚Äî declare as named `const val` or `companion object` constants.
- Remove all unused `ARG_PARAM1 / ARG_PARAM2` Fragment wizard remnants.
- No `!!` outside of the View Binding getter pattern; use `?: return`, `let`, or `requireNotNull`.

```kotlin
// ‚ùå BAD
val user = getUser()!!

// ‚úÖ GOOD
val user = getUser() ?: return
```

## Naming Conventions

| Kind | Convention | Example |
|---|---|---|
| Classes / Objects | PascalCase | `PostRepository`, `HomeFragment` |
| Functions / properties | camelCase | `fetchPosts()`, `isLoading` |
| Constants | SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE | `MAX_PAGE_SIZE` |
| Layout files | `fragment_*`, `item_*`, `activity_*` | `fragment_home.xml` |
| Drawable / icons | `ic_*`, `bg_*`, `img_*` | `ic_like.xml` |
| LiveData backing field | `_name` (private mutable) + `name` (public immutable) | `_posts` / `posts` |

## Formatting & Spacing

- Indent: **4 spaces** (no tabs).
- Max line length: **120 characters**.
- One blank line between class members; two blank lines between top-level declarations.
- Opening brace on the **same line**; closing brace on its own line.
- No trailing whitespace.
- Section dividers (`// ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ`) are acceptable but keep them consistent; prefer them only in large files.

## Lint

- **Zero lint errors** ‚Äî fix every `error`-level lint issue before committing.
- Address `warning`-level issues unless suppressing with a documented `@SuppressLint` reason.
- Never suppress lint without an inline comment explaining why.

```kotlin
// ‚ùå BAD
@SuppressLint("SetTextI18n")
fun bind() { label.text = "Page " + page }

// ‚úÖ GOOD ‚Äî or better: use string resources
@SuppressLint("SetTextI18n") // concatenation is non-translatable by design; numeric suffix
fun bind() { label.text = "Page $page" }
```

## Dependency Injection

The project uses manual construction (no Hilt/Dagger). Until a DI framework is introduced:

- Instantiate dependencies in `*ViewModelFactory`, **not** inside the ViewModel body.
- Pass repositories as constructor parameters to ViewModels.
- Never call `AppDatabase.getInstance(context)` inside a Fragment.

## Logging

- Use `Log.d/e/w` with a consistent `TAG` constant per class.
- Remove or guard debug logs behind `BuildConfig.DEBUG` before merging.
- Avoid emoji in log messages ‚Äî they hinder log filtering in Logcat.

```kotlin
companion object { private const val TAG = "HomeViewModel" }

// ‚úÖ
if (BuildConfig.DEBUG) Log.d(TAG, "Posts loaded: ${posts.size}")
```
